(360, 'Notes:: **Views:** Yashi: Track for us, should pursue via DeVC **Spiky: **0 **EF/FF: **FF **Founder Archetype: **6 **FMF: **7 **Thesis: **5 + Interesting and very pedigreed team, Dhruv didn’t speak much so don’t have a read on him, Mohak is articulate + For a new startup 12 months out, very good logos and early pilots – great pipeline so far + seemed very high on hunger and hustle ? unclear on their tech moat and thesis area – highly competitive with AI picking up ? Selling to discoms and cracking govt contracts isn’t easy – will need a sales team and ecosystem connects **Notes:** **Product Development** - Thesis was 3 use cases: - Trust deficit: won’t give data, show immediate value via weather which is readily available - RE forecasting - Load forecasting: needs historical load data - Congestion mgmt: both and network nodes - Magic happens when you start doing scheduling and dispatch for utility - Generator etc - 5-10M+ ACV potential - Structured use cases sequentially with increasing data requirements: - Renewable forecasting (limited data needed) - Load forecasting (requires historical load data) - Congestion management (needs both plus network topology) - Goal: Address trust deficit, gain trust, then provide more value - High-value opportunity in scheduling and dispatch decisions ($5-10M+ ACV) **Traction and Customer Pipeline** - Tata Power - Already using software - can add on as a layer - What is landing? Sales motion? Pilot and POC: what are they looking at? - Output ...'),
(361, 'Meeting with [Vupil Vaibhav](https://in.linkedin.com/in/vipulvaibhaw) (Founding Engineer @ Pre6 Ai) 2025-07-13T13:54:00.000+05:30: Reflections - Extremely thoughtful / outside-in / product first developer | Seems like Amod has built an A* team around him! ++ Wants to start up someday, doesn’t know what to do ++ Writes developer focused content (including video) Notes 1. About Vipul 1. Early life 1. From Patna 1. Spent 10 yrs in Pune 1. Worked at shitty services companies before taking a 1 year sabbatical 1. Content 1. Started doing a podcast to speak with founders of new age DB companies 1. Amod was an Angel in Tiger DB whose CoFo came on Vipul’s pod 1. Amod connected with Vipul via the same 1. Software Engineering 1. Interested in the hardware side of the world 1. Believes that too many abstractions have caused modern software engineers to not understand hardware 1. Next layer of compute performance improvements will come from hardware utilization 1. About Amod 1. Vipul asked him: “How do I know I’m not joining a rich person’s side project?” 1. Amod said: “you’ll see me in office everyday” 1. And, Amod has been coming to office everyday 1. has STOPPED posting on X and other social platforms 1. About Pre6 1. Thesis: as CPU cost is going up, more companies will switch from cloud to on-prem AND more software engineers will start to care about hardware / architecture choice of hardware while running software 1. Team has been hired from Amod’s network 1. Total 10 people including...'),
(362, 'Meeting Prep — 2026-03-06: ## Conversation Prep Research — ProactAI ### Auto-generated on 2026-03-06 02:40 IST ## Founders & Background *Adarsh Jain* — Co-Founder CEO ## Company Synopsis Source: Inbound via Prajwal Kumar (HC team) - forwarded to Aakash, Rajat, Rahul on 19 Feb 2026. Prajwal offered to intro if of interest. Founder: Adarsh Jain (Co-founder & CEO) Team Profile: Company: ProactAI ## Market Map ### Web Research: - Top Proactiv Alternatives, Competitors See how Proactiv compares to similar products. Proactiv&#x27;s top competitors include Dr. https://www.cbinsights.com/company/proactiv/alternatives-competitors - Proactiv - 2025 Company Profile & Competitors - Tracxn Proactiv has not raised any funding rounds yet. ... Our Google Chrome extension lets you view company details while browsing their websitesInstall Tracxn Extension · Top competitors of Proactiv includ https://tracxn.com/d/companies/proactiv/__HVBhvz6OvRIZGbuqsiWrXdf3q02Xc_E2-tGuWw5w58Y - proactiv.com Competitors - Top Sites Like proactiv.com | Similarweb proactiv.com top 10 competitors &amp; alternatives. Analyze sites like proactiv.com ranked by keyword and audience similarity for free with one click here https://www.similarweb.com/website/proactiv.com/competitors/ - Top The Proactiv Company Competitors and Alternatives | Craft.co The Proactiv Company&#x27;s main competitors include <strong>Wella, Biossance, Neftis Laboratorios and Delarange</strong>. Compare The Proactiv Company to its competitors by ...'),
(365, 'Notes:: **Founders** [**Sandeep Aggarwal**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sandeep-aggarwal-1a827415/)[** **](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sandeep-aggarwal-1a827415/)- Head Banking and Partnership Alliances @ PayU (~4 yrs), Head Sales and Portfolio - Merchant Acq Biz @ IndusInd (2.5 yrs) , Head ECom and Key Accounts North and East @ Axis Bank (9.5 yrs), Manager Key Accounts @ HDFC Bank (1 yr) [**Arvind Singh**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/arvind-singh-a324341a/) - Business Head Commercial and Business Cards @ IndusInd (~9 yrs 8 mos), TMCs and Alliances @ Axis Bank (6 yrs),  Business Manager Corporate Cards @ ICICI (2 yrs) **Overview- ** Solving B2B payment workflows and  working capital lines using commercial cards. Planning to start by focusing on the travel segment as a vertical, allow smaller OTAs and travel agents to access credit while booking flights (will tie up with IATA over here). **Views** **TT- Weak Maybe** **Overall- **Interesting thesis vis-a-vis B2B payments and vertical focused workflow solving (travel), However founder archetype (Sales profile + muddled thought process ) + lack of courage of conviction( neither of the founders have quit yet) breaks it for me in the first meeting. Will need consistent rockstar refs to consider for MPI Seed. + Interesting thesis- B2B payments + verticalized value using commercial cards --- starting with travel + Founders have spent 10 K hours in the space (albeit in sales roles) ?Muddled thought process- not completely clear on the...')
